tle=Meet Prajakta Koli and everything insane that makes her 'Insane' |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/lifestyle/life-style/meet-prajakta-koli-and-everything-insane-that-makes-her-mostly-sane-5290115/ |website=indianexpress|date=3 August 2018 }}</ref> She is popularly known by her [[YouTube]] name \"MostlySane\". Her videos are mostly comical takes on her observation of everyday life situations.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mid-day.com/articles/a-chat-with-emerging-youtube-sensation-prajakta-koli/17165191|title=A chat with emerging YouTube sensation Prajakta Koli|date=2016-04-24|work=mid-day|access-date=2018-03-28}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nShe worked at Fever 104 FM radio station in Mumbai as an intern for about a year.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.scoopwhoop.com/prajakta-koli-mostly-sane/|title=Meet Prajakta Koli, The Funny Girl From Mumbai The Internet Is Falling In Love With|last=ScoopWhoop|date=2018-01-30|work=ScoopWhoop|access-date=2018-03-28|language=En}}</ref> She launched her YouTube channel on 12 February 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/lifestyle/story/queen-of-content-prajakta-koli-takes-us-inside-her-life-as-a-popular-youtuber-1239456-2018-05-23|title=Queen of content Prajakta Koli takes us inside her life as a popular YouTuber|website=indiatoday}}</ref>\n\nKoli has collaborated with mainstream Bollywood actors like [[Kareena Kapoor|Kareena Kapoor Khan]], [[Saif Ali Khan|Saif Ali Khan,]] [[Ayushmann Khurrana|Ayushmann Khurana]], [[Nawazuddin Siddiqui]], [[Vicky Kaushal]], [[Kajol]], [[Ajay Devgn]], [[Varun Dhawan]], [[Alia Bhatt]] and more along with digital stars like [[Lilly Singh]], [[Collins Key]], [[Bhuvan Bam]], [[Ashish Chanchlani|Ashish Chanchalani]], Be YouNick,Sanya Malhotra among others.  <ref>{{cite web |title=Responsibility Has Become A Huge Focus For YouTube: Susan Wojcicki |url=http://www.forbesindia.com/article/special/responsibility-has-become-a-huge-focus-for-youtube-susan-wojcicki/53085/1 |website=Forbes India |accessdate=27 February 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Kareena Kapoor Khan digs ground; video goes viral |url=https://www.mid-day.com/articles/kareena-kapoor-khan-digs-ground-video-goes-viral/21848178 |website=mid-day |accessdate=27 February 2020 |language=en |date=5 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nKoli has performed at YouTube FanFest in Delhi in 2018 and in Mumbai in 2016 & 2019<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.afaqs.com/news/digital/54782_uber-eats-vivo-5-star-do-tamasha-at-youtube-fanfest-2019|title=Uber Eats, Vivo, 5 Star do tamasha at YouTube FanFest 2019|website=afaqs!|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thequint.com/neon/web-culture/youtube-fanfest-2018-delhi|title=The Quint Feat. Bb Ki Vines, Carryminati, Sejal Kumar, Mostlysane|date=2018-03-19|website=The Quint|language=en|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref>. In May 2018, she was announced as the Indian Ambassador for YouTube's global initiative, 'Creators For Change', which deals with problems like hate speech, [[xenophobia]] and extremism. She made a music video named \"No Offence\" for her YouTube Creators For Change Project, which was shown in the [[United Nations]] as part of their International Day of Tolerance where she represented India.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.news18.com/news/tech/aib-niharika-nm-mostlysane-join-youtube-creators-for-change-program-1743153.html|title=AIB, Niharika NM, MostlySane Join YouTube's 'Creators For Change' Program|work=News18|access-date=2018-05-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/YouTube/status/993896784207536128|title=YouTube on Twitter|website=Twitter|language=en|access-date=2018-05-10}}</ref> In December 2018, Koli recorded a national TV commercial for [[WhatsApp]] which deals with the prevention of propaganda and spreading fake news through the messaging app.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.afaqs.com/news/story/54044_WhatsApps-first-India-specific-TVCs-attack-fake-news|title=WhatsApp's first India-specific TVCs attack fake news|date=2018-12-03|website=www.afaqs.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-12-14}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=WhatsApp|title=WhatsApp - \u091c\u0928\u094d\u092e\u0926\u093f\u0928 \u092c\u093e\u0901\u091f\u093f\u092f\u0947, \u0939\u0902\u0938\u0940-\u092e\u091c\u093e\u0915 \u092c\u093e\u0901\u091f\u093f\u092f\u0947, \u0916\u0941\u0936\u093f\u092f\u093e\u0901 \u092c\u093e\u0901\u091f\u093f\u092f\u0947, \u0905\u092b\u0935\u093e\u0939\u0947\u0902 \u0928\u0939\u0940\u0902.|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qqHrZ5C1poY|access-date=2018-12-14}}</ref> In February 2019 she was part of [[Forbes]]' list of 30 under 30 and in [[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]] Business Magazine's list of Women of Worth<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wow.outlookbusiness.com/tag/prajakta-koli/|title=Prajakta Koli \u2013 Outlook Business WoW|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref> and Entrepreneur India's list of 35 under 35<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.entrepreneur.com/slideshow/327768|title=Entrepreneur Reveals its 35 Under 35 Class of 2019|last=Sabharwal|first=Punita|date=2019-02-09|website=Entrepreneur|language=en|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref> along with winning Cosmopolitan magazine's YouTuber of the Year award<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.headlinesoftoday.com/headlines/cosmopolitan-awards-winners-2019-see-the-full-report.html|title=Cosmopolitan Awards Winners 2019: See The Full Report|last=Satote|first=Monika|date=2019-03-27|website=Headlines of Today|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref>.\n\nIn April 2019, [[Susan Wojcicki]] sat down with Prajakta for an interview which was the first creator led interview Susan Wojcicki did globally<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.forbesindia.com/article/special/responsibility-has-become-a-huge-focus-for-youtube-susan-wojcicki/53085/1|title=Responsibility has become a huge focus for YouTube: Susan Wojcicki|website=Forbes India|language=en|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref>. Later that year she interviewed comedian [[Russell Peters]] to promote his world tour, Deported<ref>{{Citation|title=Russell Peters Called Me A Lallu {{!}} #RealTalkTuesday{{!}} MostlySane|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-nLv87mfRlY|language=en|access-date=2020-01-03}}</ref> and followed it up with Jamaican sprinter [[Yohan Blake]]<ref>{{Citation|title=Yohan Blake: The Fastest Man On Earth {{!}} #RealTalkTuesday {{!}} MostlySane|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=il7JF5VpxXw|language=en|access-date=2020-01-03}}</ref>. Koli was also invited by [[The Walt Disney Company|Disney]] to travel to Singapore for the premier of Captain Marvel, where she interviewed [[Brie Larson]] and [[Samuel L. Jackson|Samuel L Jackson]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iwmbuzz.com/digital/releases-digital/captain-marvel-aka-brie-larson-exclusive-rendezvous-prajakta-koli-aka-mostlysane-singapore/2019/03/09|title=Captain Marvel aka Brie Larson has an exclusive rendezvous with Prajakta Koli aka MostlySane in Singapore!|last=Team|first=Author: Editorial|date=2019-03-09|website=IWMBuzz|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-23}}</ref> \n\nKoli was invited on [[Kareena Kapoor Khan]]'s show What Women Want wherein she spoke about her journey on the digital space<ref>{{Citation|last=Ishq|title=Prajakta Koli & Kareena - Performance Pressure {{!}} Dabur Amla What Women Want {{!}} 104.8 Ishq|date=2019-02-25|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AqpV87ZGja0&t=16s|access-date=2019-03-08}}</ref>. She has been a part of the YouTube original series Off The Page with Lage Raho Munna Bhai alongside [[Sanjay Dutt]], [[Vidya Balan]], [[Arshad Warsi]], [[Boman Irani]] and other cast members<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.republicworld.com/entertainment-news/bollywood-news/sanjay-dutt-and-the-lage-raho-munna-bhai-cast-reunite-for-off-the-page|title=Sanjay Dutt & the Lage Raho Munna Bhai cast reunite for Off The Page|last=World|first=Republic|website=Republic World|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref>. In October 2019 she performed at Social Nation in Jio Garden, Mumbai<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.exchange4media.com/industry-briefing-news/is-social-nation-the-vidcon-of-india-100194.html|title=Is Social Nation the VidCon of India? - Exchange4media|website=Indian Advertising Media & Marketing News \u2013 exchange4media|language=en|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref> \n\nIn January 2020 Koli was included in Grazia Magazine's annual Cool list<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B64tlNYB8do/|title=GRAZIA India on Instagram: \"With the whole digital wave that's taken over, thinking YouTube can't be a real career is just not sensible,\" says @mostlysane. We teamed\u2026\"|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2020-01-04}}</ref>.  \n\nIn 2020 Koli announced the launch of her [[YouTube Originals]] show 'Pretty Fit', where she interviews other celebrities including [[Kareena Kapoor]], [[Neha Kakkar]], [[Sanya Malhotra]], [[RJ Malishka]], [[Mithila Palkar]] and [[Sumukhi Suresh]], who are made to perform various tasks. The first episode was released on 21 January.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.socialsamosa.com/2020/01/youtube-fitness-themed-original-show-indian-market-pretty-fit/|title=YouTube announces fitness-themed Original show in Indian market|last=Samosa|first=Social|date=2020-01-17|website=Social Samosa|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-20}}</ref> Another YouTube Originals series starting in 2020, Creators For Change, features Koli together with two other YouTube content creators, [[Liza Koshy]], and Thembe Mahlaba. They interview well-known people about issues that are important to them; the first installment includes a discussion with [[Michelle Obama]] about education for girls.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/01/creators-change-michelle-obama-youtube-1202834898/|title=YouTube \u2018Creators for Change\u2019 Anticipates Michelle Obama Interview \u2013 TCA|last=Haithman|first=Diane|last2=Haithman|first2=Diane|date=2020-01-18|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2020-01-20}}</ref>\n\n==  Social initiatives  ==\nOn [[World Mental Health Day]] in 2016, Koli launched her campaign #iPledgeToBeMe which addresses [[mental health]] well being and body shaming. She invited to share with her their experiences around body shaming. She wrote a rap song \u2018Shameless\u2019, which was released in May 2017. The video features [[Raftaar (rapper)|Raftaar]], [[Raghav Juyal]], [[RJ Malishka|RJ Mallishka]], [[Gaurav Gera]], [[Mithila Palkar]], [[Sahil Khattar]]<ref>{{Citation |last=MostlySane |title=Shameless (\u0936\u0947\u092e\u0932\u0947\u0938) by Prajakta Koli ft. Raftaar {{!}} MostlySane {{!}} #iPledgeToBeMe |date=2017-05-25 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H3vA0EJQ2mo |access-date=2019-03-08}}</ref> among others.\n\nShe has been part of campaigns such as #GirlsCount for [[ONE Campaign|One.Org]] where she spoke about the importance of girl's education. She also participated in YouTube's ''Safer Internet Week'' where she addressed cyber-bullying. In November 2018 she collaborated with YouTube Impact Labs to promote education for girls<ref>{{Citation |last=YouTube Social Impact |title=MostlySane Supports Girl's Education (HI) |date=2018-10-10 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4XoP44U3H8s |access-date=2019-03-28}}</ref>. She was also one of the four YouTube creators from India invited by the Obama Foundation to attend the town hall meeting by [[Barack Obama|President Obama]]<ref>{{Citation |last=MostlySane |title=Attending the Obama Foundation Town Hall with Fellow youTubers! {{!}} MostlyVlogs {{!}} MostlySane |date=2017-12-09 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R328sedrAa8 |access-date=2019-03-08}}</ref>. In September 2019 Koli traveled to New York as a delegate for Goalkeepers an initiative by [[Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation]]<ref>{{Citation|title=My NewYork Vlog {{!}} #RealTalkTuesday {{!}} MostlySane|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vNBf_FkpE_A|language=en|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref>.   \n\nIn 2019, Prajakta, associated with Anshula Kapoor's crowdfunding platform, Fankind to raise money for The Banyan Foundation a charity based out of Chennai which deals with mental health issues.<ref>{{Citation|chapter=How to Raise Money|date=2016-11-25|pages=19\u201336|publisher=John Wiley & Sons, Inc.|isbn=978-1-119-25979-4|doi=10.1002/9781119259794.ch2|title=Venture Deals}}</ref>    \n\n== Awards and recognition ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Year\n!Publication\n!Award/Recognition\n!Results\n!Ref\n|-\n|2018\n|24 FPS International Animation Awards\n|YouTube Sensation (Digital Content)\n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.aninews.in/news/business/business/young-talent-sparkles-at-the-16th-edition-of-maac-24fps-awards201812191820030001/ |title=Young Talent Sparkles at the 16th Edition of MAAC 24FPS Awards |website=www.aninews.in |language=en |access-date=2019-03-20}}</ref>\n|-\n|2019\n|[[Forbes India]]\n|30 Under 30 2019\n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.forbesindia.com/article/30-under-30-2019/prajakta-koli-digital-diva/52421/1 |title=Prajakta Koli: Digital diva |website=Forbes India |language=en |access-date=2019-03-20}}</ref>\n|-\n|2019\n|[[Entrepreneur India]]\n|35 Under 35 2019\n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.entrepreneur.com/slideshow/327768 |title=Entrepreneur Reveals its 35 Under 35 Class of 2019 |last=Sabharwal |first=Punita |date=2019-02-09 |website=Entrepreneur |language=en |access-date=2019-03-20}}</ref>\n\n|-\n|2019\n|Outlook Business\n|Women of Worth (WoW)\n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.headlinesoftoday.com/entertainment/prajakta-koli-is-a-woman-of-worth-check-out-the-story-of-home-grown-talent.html |title=Prajakta Koli is a Woman of Worth ! : Check Out The Story of Home-Grown Talent. |last=Satote |first=Monika |date=2019-03-10 |website=Headlines of Today - Breaking News, Latest News, World News, India News, Cricket, Videos & Photos |language=en-US |access-date=2019-03-20}}</ref>\n|-\n|2019\n|Cosmopolitan Magazine India\n|YouTuber Of The year\n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{Citation |last=