{"title_page": "Xavier B. Fern\u00e1ndez", "text_new": "'''Xavier B. Fern\u00e1ndez''' (born 1960, [[Barcelona]]) is a [[Spaniards|Spanish]] writer and journalist. He studied information science at the [[Universidad Aut\u00f3noma de Barcelona]] and went on to work for a variety of local papers, among them ''Els 4 Cantons'', ''El Punt'', and ''Diari de Terrassa''. In 1994, he made his debut as a screenwriter, penning scripts for episodes of the TV series ''Detective Bogey''. He also worked on series such as ''El patito feo'', ''Los tres ositos'' and ''Bandolero''. In 20006, the Mexican publisher Resistencia brought out his novel ''Kensington Gardens'', which became a cult favorite of punk and emo teenagers. He has published half a dozen books till date.<ref>[http://www.agenciabalcells.com/autores/autor/xavier-b-fernandez/ Bio]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fernandez, Xavier B.}}\n[[Category:Spanish writers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1960 births]]\n\n\n{{Spain-writer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Xavier B. Fern\u00e1ndez''' (born 1960, [[Barcelona]]) is a [[Spaniards|Spanish]] writer and journalist. He studied information science at the [[Universidad Aut\u00f3noma de Barcelona]] and went on to work for a variety of local papers, among them ''Els 4 Cantons'', ''El Punt'', and ''Diari de Terrassa''. In 1994, he made his debut as a screenwriter, penning scripts for episodes of the TV series ''Detective Bogey''. He also worked on series such as ''El patito feo'', ''Los tres ositos'' and ''Bandolero''. In 20006, the Mexican publisher Resistencia brought out his novel ''Kensington Gardens'', which became a cult favorite of punk and emo teenagers. He has published half a dozen books till date.<ref>[http://www.agenciabalcells.com/autores/autor/xavier-b-fernandez/ Bio]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fernandez, Xavier B.}}\n[[category:Spanish writers]]\n[[Category:Living